>> Minimal record set for the AgentDojo banking suite, attached to the
>> MCP tools served by clean/rig/agentdojo-mcp.
>>
>> This is a teaching example — the production records and trust modes
>> live in clean/bench/domains/banking/records.mld. The shape is the
>> same; this version is trimmed to the smallest set that demonstrates
>> the record-attachment pattern.

>> ── Read records ──

>> A transaction. `id`/`recipient` are facts (control-arg eligible);
>> `amount`/`date`/`subject` are content.
record @transaction = {
  facts: [id: handle, recipient: string?],
  data: {
    trusted: [amount: number?, date: string?],
    untrusted: [subject: string?]
  },
  key: id,
  read: [{ value: "id" }, { value: "recipient" }, amount, subject, date]
}

>> The user's IBAN. Singleton fact-bearing value.
record @iban_value = {
  facts: [value: string],
  key: value,
  read: [{ value: "value" }]
}

>> ── Write input records ──
>>
>> Input records replace the fork's `controlArgs`/`payloadArgs` split.
>> Fact fields become control args; data fields become payload args.

record @send_money_inputs = {
  facts: [recipient: string],
  data: {
    trusted: [amount: number, date: string],
    untrusted: [subject: string]
  },
  validate: "strict"
}

export { @transaction, @iban_value, @send_money_inputs }
